# UI Layer: Decompose + MVI + App Navigation/DI

## 1) What this module must produce
- Decompose `*RootComponent` for the feature (top-level or nested navigation inside the feature).
- MVI `Store` + `*Component` that exposes immutable UI state and accepts UI intents/events.
- Compose `*RootMain` and screen composables that only render state + forward events.
- UI-level DI factories (as `ComponentFactory` extension functions) to instantiate stores/components/root component.

## 2) Decompose wiring (Root level)
- `*RootComponent` should expose immutable navigation/state, typically:
  - `val stack: Value<ChildStack<*, Child>>`
- `Default*RootComponent` should implement child creation via `childFactory = ::child`.
- Keep per-feature navigation logic inside the feature root (not in the global app root).

## 3) MVI wiring (Store -> Component -> Screen)
- Implement a `Store` (mvikotlin) and a `*Component` that:
  - exposes `val state: Value<Store.State>` (use `store.asValue()` pattern)
  - exposes `fun onIntent(intent: Store.Intent)` (delegate to `store.accept(intent)`)
- Subscribe to labels inside the component using a lifecycle/coroutine scope from Decompose/Essenty (see `coroutineScope()` usage).
- Map store labels to UI callbacks (navigation/close) via parameters passed into the component (no direct navigation from composables).

## 4) Compose must be dumb + feature-isolated DI
- `*RootMain` must wrap UI in isolated DI context:
  - `KoinIsolatedContext(context = IsolatedKoinContext.koinApplication())`
- UI composables should:
  - only read the passed `component.state` (or subscribe-as-state from `component.stack`)
  - call `component.onIntent(...)` / forward events
  - not access Koin/DI and not create stores/components directly.

## 5) UI -> App navigation contract (use AppFeature)
- For cross-feature navigation, UI must signal intent using:
  - `AppFeature` from `common/core-navigation`
- In store label handling, call the injected callback:
  - `onNavigateToFeature(AppFeature.<YourFeature>)`
- Never push navigation configs directly from the UI feature; the global app decides how `AppFeature` maps to `AppRootConfig`.

## 6) When you add a new UI feature to the app (global integration checklist)
When editing a `*-ui` module, also update (at minimum) these app-level points:
- `common/core-navigation/AppFeature.kt`
  - add a new `AppFeature` entry for your feature
- `composeApp/.../roating/AppRootComponent.kt`
  - extend `AppRootConfig` with a new configuration object
  - extend the `child(...)` `when (config)` branch to create `create<YourFeature>RootComponent(...)`
- `composeApp/.../roating/mapper/AppRootMapper.kt`
  - map `AppFeature.<YourFeature>` -> `AppRootConfig.<YourFeature>` in `toConfig()`
- `composeApp/.../di/AppModules.kt`
  - add your feature `*-domain`, `*-data`, `*-data-network` Koin modules

## 7) Isolation rule (avoid tight coupling)
- `*-ui` must not depend on `*-data` / `*-data-network` directly.
- UI features must remain isolated: they plug into the app only through `AppFeature` + factories/config mapping.

